title: Portland Cello Project hits up Main Street Studios
text: Print this article Advertisement The Portland Cello Project will perform at 7 p.m. on Friday at Main Street Studios, 207 W. Main St. Since the group’s inception in late 2007, the Portland Cello Project has wowed audiences all over the country with extravagant performances. The group has played venues including “A Prairie Home Companion,” parties on loading docks in New York City, symphony halls coast to coast and punk-rock clubs. The group, which can change from four to 12 cellos, mixes genres and blurs musical lines and perceptions wherever it goes. Tickets are $20-$100 at mainstreetstudios.co, the door, or by calling 844-207-6246.
